    <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><font size="2"><font face="Microsoft Sans Serif" size="2">

<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Glykus Helmir</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Glykus Helmir">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b> 66-66<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font> Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font> Rare_Monster<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font> Drunder<br>

<br><b>Special Attacks:</b><br>
<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=spellsbrdcomplete&eqspells.spell_name=%22Gravel%20Rain%22">Gravel Rain</a>
<br>







<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font><br>- Hits for ~850 per attack.<BR>- Spawns in Boar Pens zone out.<BR>- Spawns adds when he is attacked.<BR>- Point Blank AE is magic based (-300) and has a radius of 50. It does up to 250 points of Direct Damage and snares the target by 55% for a whopping 30 minutes. It is a curse with 72 counters.<BR><BR><b>Spawn and Scouting</b><BR><BR>Glykus Helmir spawns in the Boar Pens in Tactics. This is where the Stampede begins, but if you are inside of the pens they will not affect you. He spawns right next to the zone out in this area. Any character can invis down to here to check, so long as they are careful to avoid any wraiths, as the wraiths see invisibility. Glykus also sees invisible, so do not get too close to him.<BR><BR><b>What You Need</b><BR><BR>With decent gear you can kill Glykus with a single group. Players without great gear or experience will likely want to bring two or three groups to this encounter.<BR><BR><b>Preparation</b><BR><BR>You will want to first gather in the room outside of the pens to buff up. Cast magic resistance buffs on all characters. His AE can be resisted but it has a -300 modifier, which means you will need high resist to avoid it. If you have any bards at your disposal place one with the main tank to help him resist the spell. The damage on the AE is only 250, but the snare is annoying, and will cause the tank problems in regaining aggro if he loses it and Glykus ping pongs on to someone else. <BR><BR>Clear the pens except for Glykus by pulling to the outside room. Once the pens are clear you can move the raid to just inside of the pens.  <BR><BR>At least one person needs to be assigned as the kiter for the boars. Bards generally make the best kiters because they can use AE to aggro the boars on the move.<BR><BR><b>The Fight</b><BR><BR>Place the bulk of the raid just inside of the pens. Have the main tank stand a ways ahead of everyone else to intercept Glykus on the way in. Have the assigned kiter stand a ways behind eveyrone else. It is very important that they do not get snared. If you have anyone present who possesses Remove Greater Curse, they need to be on kiter watch in case the snare does land.<BR><BR>Pull Glykus to the party and have the main tank intercept him out of range of the others until he gets an aggro lock. Once Glykus is pulled he will spawn about 8 little boars. Once that happens the kiter needs to aggro these mobs and then kite them further in to the pens and run around in circles. The boars don't hit very hard but they are an annoyance and you can not afford to allow them to get on to your casters. <BR><BR>Once aggro has been locked on Glykus and the kiter has the boars under control the rest of the raid can assist. It's a relatively easy fight. He does not rampage and only hits for around 850 points of damage per attack. <BR><BR>After Glykus is dead be sure to cure everyone of the snare. It lasts for 30 minutes and is very annoying. Remove Greater Curse can cure it.<br>

<br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>
<font color=#d2d200>Ornate Cloth Robe Pattern</font><br>
<A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Blood Runed Battle Wand%22">Blood Runed Battle Wand</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Split Blade of Destruction%22">Split Blade of Destruction</A><br>

